
- reading list

// A small corpus tracking books I have read, what each is about,
// who wrote them, what they cite, and a one-line takeaway.
// Uses only arrows that ship in the default SSTconfig:
//   (about)     — the topic of
//   (by)        — the author of
//   (bib-cite)  — cites (as a bibtex-style citation)
//   (note)      — a note or remark about

 :: books, topics, authors ::

 Thinking Fast and Slow     (about)    decision making
        "                   (about)    dual-process cognition
        "                   (about)    heuristics
        "                   (by)       Daniel Kahneman
        "                   (bib-cite) Judgment under Uncertainty
        "                   (note)     two systems, one of them lazy, both of them you

 Judgment under Uncertainty (about)    heuristics
        "                   (about)    cognitive bias
        "                   (by)       Daniel Kahneman
        "                   (by)       Amos Tversky
        "                   (note)     the anchor is almost always the wrong number

 Superforecasting           (about)    decision making
        "                   (about)    prediction
        "                   (by)       Philip Tetlock
        "                   (bib-cite) Thinking Fast and Slow
        "                   (note)     calibration beats cleverness over long horizons

 The Dictators Handbook     (about)    political coalitions
        "                   (about)    incentive structures
        "                   (by)       Bruce Bueno de Mesquita
        "                   (note)     rulers survive by keeping a small coalition paid

 Seeing Like a State        (about)    central planning
        "                   (about)    legibility
        "                   (about)    incentive structures
        "                   (by)       James C. Scott
        "                   (note)     what the centre can measure is not what the edge actually does

 The Origins of Political Order (about) state formation
        "                   (about)    political coalitions
        "                   (by)       Francis Fukuyama
        "                   (bib-cite) Seeing Like a State
        "                   (note)     impersonal institutions are hard to build and easy to lose

 Thinking in Systems        (about)    feedback loops
        "                   (about)    complexity
        "                   (about)    decision making
        "                   (by)       Donella Meadows
        "                   (note)     most problems are the shape of a feedback loop
